Review.Titre: Fidelity UF-A × 1 are a bad product
Review.Contenu: I ordered the Fidelity UF-A × 1 for my Airpods pro 2 thinking that they might be a better fit than the original ear tips. Wrong. So very wrong! Regardless the size I chose, regardless how well I try to seat them in my ears, the result is a very poor seal and therefore a very poor ANC performance. At least, know I know that the original ear tips are actually very good. I’m sorry to say, but the Fidelity tips are absolute cheap crap.

Review.Titre: DO NOT waste your money on these. Worthless purchase.
Review.Contenu: Not even remotely close to working as advertised. Doesn’t improve bass quality, does not fit more comfortably in your ear than the stock silicone ear pieces. Threw them away after a week of use, incredibly disappointed. Product is not worth $20. I feel like these should be given away free at gas stations.

Paying this much for the Bose ear buds plus the cost of the ear tune and not being able to use this function was not worth the money. Plus the sound quality was severely diminished when they did work. I would not recommend this product if you have the Bose quite comfort model.

Review.Titre: Honestly this took way too long
Review.Contenu: Honestly this took way too long. It seemed like i couldn't get ahold of an employee and then was told the molds I sent in had no order #. Ok, so the one on the bag was covered by UPS. But the pic they sent me didnt show the box the molds were in in the package. That had the order # on it. OR the package slip that had thr Order #, address, and instructions, that was also in that package. The molds just werent in an envelope and thats all. They'd have been destroyed! Missed the time frame for it to be the gift I was hoping to give. Now They've switched buds because the ones she had didn't fit so theyre useless... Other than that, Its my understanding they fit at least, and they eventually came in so theres that too.

Review.Titre: Tried the ear pieces twice- two nights…
Review.Contenu: Tried the ear pieces twice- two nights …neither time did they diminish environmental sounds… very disappointing.
20 dollars for this? 6 foam eartips that do basically the same thing as the originals? i regret buying this, it was a waste if money

Review.Titre: Product works but overall experience not the best
Review.Contenu: I can confirm they work, but do take a few tries to figure out how they fit in your ear. The reason for 3 stars vs more was my overall experience. Before purchasing, I reached out to Eartune asking for the time I can expect the product to ship and was quoted 3-4 weeks. With this in mind I waited until 4 weeks to check in as I had not received any updates. At this time, they responded letting me know my ear molds were smaller than normal and asked if I still wanted to proceed and I let them know yes. I also shared I would be traveling in 2 weeks and was hoping to have them by the date I would be leaving. After a week I still had no updates on shipping and reached out again. They got back to me 2 days later which was the Friday before my trip (leaving Monday) saying they had shipped that day. As expected this was not ready by Monday and I didn’t receive it until Thursday. I had to have someone pick it up for me as I was out of town and overall just frustrated with the lack of communication. If you are interested in purchasing the product, it does work but expect delays in shipping.

Overall, these replacement ear tips are better than the Apple tips. However, these also start falling out like the Apple ones, but last a bit longer inside the ear canal. I purchased the “Mix” sized black tips. The Medium size fits the most comfortable, in my experience with Eartune memory foam Air Pod Pro tips. At this point, I’ll keep using the Eartunes, for the sake of not spending more money on an already expensive product like the Air Pods Pro.

Review.Titre: The company shipped exactly what I…
Review.Contenu: The company shipped exactly what I ordered in a timely manner. The problem is of my own making-I wear an x-small ear tip and I hoped the small sized eartune would suitable. Sadly, it is not hence the 3 star review.  I cannot evaluate the product performance but I believe the company produces a quality product.

While I appreciate the product, the communication style was more cold and slow vs warm and responsive. The molds I was told were not right yet the product fits perfectly. The time it took to get the plugs was over 3 months. Way too long for what they are.

Review.Titre: Was sent a request to review how they…
Review.Contenu: Was sent a request to review how they did on my order. Well considering my order hasn’t arrived and is currently sitting in Puerto Rico “I live in St. Louis” so you can see why this would be a problem.

Review.Titre: Much Better than the apple ear pieces
Review.Contenu: Much Better than the apple ear pieces, however, they still don't stay in my ears very well when walking.  Very comfortable I could wear all day.  In the end they saved me from buying NEW earpods for now at least.

Review.Titre: Took a long time to get here
Review.Contenu: Took a long time to get here. No shipping follow-up towards the end. The large size, is not equivalent to others larges, and are not even wearable in my ears.
Definitely stay in the ear better, bass was slightly dulled down compared to regular air pod pro tips, sound cancellation as well but overall not a bad product

These earplugs work pretty well. There are a couple of issues I have with them. First of all it seems the leashes are too short. I have only used them with my hooded wetsuit. They seem to hurt my ears under my hood. It might be better without the hood.
Service was quick, doesn't fit as well as I had anticipated, but this could be a result of the mold provided to Eartune.

To obtain a great fit these foam ear tips possible could be shaped differently.  While I realize they are universal fit maybe a somewhat oval shape might be better for some people. Possibly seek the help of hearing professionals as Au.D or MDs.

I like these, they did what they needed to do. I was able to hear instructions while gunfire was going off. The fir wasn’t bad either, it was comfortable and didn’t hurt. Once the firing was done and ear protection was removed I had 0 ringing in my ears. I would recommend these to anyone that does allot of shooting and doesn’t want to spend a ton of money.

Great in-ear custom fitted tips: they were well molded and fit extremely well to my ear canal.Entire process took a long time. You need to schedule an appointment at their Santa Cruz location for the fitting, then it takes 4 weeks from the fitting until you receive the final product.

Review.Titre: Custom Tips for Campfire Audio Ara
Review.Contenu: The tips were well made; the fit well and are very comfortable, and they do not alter the sound alot, I honestly think it sounds better. Giving only 4 stars tho since it took a bit longer than 3 weeks before shipping started, altho shipping was fast given that I live at the other side of the globe. Overall a great experience, would definitely buy again in the future.

I like the product overall, but... It's much better than the silicone options Apple included.  Having said that, I don't like the sizing options and I don't like that I have to spend $20 to get a multi size kit.  I wish they had several multisize kits, available in a single color to keep costs down.  Like an xs, s, m or a m, l, xl.  Three options close to what you think you need for like $10.  I got the medium and it's better than the silicone, but I think I needed the large for a better fit.

Review.Titre: Great product and glad you make it!!!
Review.Contenu: Great product so far; thank you for providing AirPod custom tips to the market!  Two suggestions:Clearly label the AirPods / AirPods Pro versions on your website (like say “works with AirPods 3rd generation”) for custom tips. I imagine you may be losing sales since it isn’t clear and I hesitated for the regular AirPods. This will happen when they release new Pros soon too so I’d keep up with that. Provide a few more updates proactively since it is a long process. Getting updates a few times would let me know nothing got lost or off track.

Great company. Quality product. They take what they do seriously. It's nice that they offer an option to send all three sizes. Still doesn't fit quite right and hurts my ear eventually but its much better than the stock buds that fall out or competitor buds that I can't wear as long.

Review.Titre: My left ear canal seems to be a weird…
Review.Contenu: My left ear canal seems to be a weird shape so I thought I would try these, they are definitely better for my ear than the stock silicone tip but could be better, I was expecting them to go a bit further in but at least I can run with them in now and not worry about one falling out. Delivery took awhile but that’s probably because I had them delivered to my military base and mail is finicky here. Thanks guys!

Review.Titre: Better Comfort, Not As Good Noise Cancellation
Review.Contenu: The purchasing process on the website was a little confusing and resulted in me not getting what I ordered at first.  Eartunes has since made it right even though it was probably my fault that it was wrong in the first place.  The product itself is nice.  The foam is more comfortable than silicon pieces originally on the AirPods.  The only thing I don't like is that the foam does not block sound as well as the silicon.  This may be because I should have ordered the extra large instead of the large.  Update: Thanks to amazing support from Eartunes, I was able to get the extra large.  The extra large work better in terms of comfort and staying in place but not as good at blocking noise as the stock silicon.  The extra large is still better than the large at blocking noise for me.

Love how they snap in like oem silicone tips. Sound quality is just as good as originals, if not a bit airer. Memory foam is also quite comfortable and puts very little pressure on my ears. However claims that it can improve noise isolation are not entirely accurate unless you were unable to get a good seal before. If anything noise isolation has very slightly decreased. For me that wasn’t a deal breaker because the ANC still works about 98-99% as well as it did with the silicone tips and they actually stay in my ears! TLDR; If you just have the problem, like me, of your earbuds constantly falling out even with a good seal it will only fix that issue. Please also make a sample pack that comes with SML instead of just three packs of sss mmm lll.

Review.Titre: Directions were quite vague what does…
Review.Contenu: Directions were quite vague what does transperancy mean

They’re cumbersome at the beginning but they definitely isolate as I’d hoped they would. As a drummer suffering from a bit of tinnitus, I can appreciate the outside noise filtering that these are capable of! I’m gonna be using them a lot!!

I ordered and received my molding kit very quickly. I then waited for my earpieces to be manufactured. After the estimated production time I inquired about the status of my order and was told that there were delays in production. After another four weeks I inquired again and was told there were delays in production. My order was finally shipped after a couple more weeks and arrived before the date that the usps said it would. Well worth the wait. The ear pieces fit as promised and are everything the company has promised.

Once I was able to get them installed, they are pretty transparent and comfortable. These were a good price for molded ear plugs but I would have liked ANY documentation or instructions on which side was which, and how they should be inserted and how to use the included ear lube. It took one month to receive them after the molds were taken. It took me several minutes to figure out which way they were supposed to be oriented to fit in my ear. Also, the carrying case is really bulky, and huge compared to the size of the hearing protectors, I would appreciate a keychain type case to make sure that it goes with me easily. I'm not sure if the included ear lube needs to be used every time, if so, a container that closes instead of a ketchup pouch that leaks inside the case would be a big improvement.

*I want to preference this by saying this is my first pair of custom in-ears.* Although the product was delayed in getting to me, it fit my ears completely. However, at first I couldn’t hear out of the left ear. After careful examination, I noticed that the left ear canal had a blockage. I had to take a pin to clear out the material obstruction in the middle of the canal. This is why I gave it 4 stars and not 5. After that, I went on to use them on stage for a performance and they’re the best fit I’ve ever had.

The only reason I didn't give 5 stars is that there were no helpful instructions when my custom fit tips came.  I wasn't even sure which one was for which ear, but I figured that would become obvious.  I watched videos and even those were not helpful. They are difficult to get in the first few times but you get used to it.  One of mine is still difficult every time, but I assume that's because of my ear.It did take the 5 weeks that they say it may take and I had gotten anxious.  I also thought I was going to get a different type of case that held tips and buds.  It wasn't what I had seen on the web site/maybe a video.Customer Service responded right away when I wrote a couple of times to make sure I had done my order correctly.  A confirmation of receipt of the order/impressions would have been nice.Overall a good experience.  I'm very happy with my purchase of custom fit tips for Airpod Pros.

Review.Titre: I wish I got the xtra large tips
Review.Contenu: I wish I got the xtra large tips. I think they would fit perfectly for me,  but having never seen an XL version of foam tips before it scared me away. Great packaging, seems premium.

Review.Titre: I received product promptly and appears…
Review.Contenu: I received product promptly and appears to be of good quality. The larger of the ear cushions are still a little small but a most definitely better that the original cushions.

The ear-molds fit perfectly.  Only drawback is that the stick out further than I would have liked and I was hoping the Shure e535s would be deeper.  They sound is okay, but not as full as I had before the molds.

I purchased mine through Amazon. Definitely much more stable in my ears than the silicone tips that come with the AirPod Pros. I wish they came in white. I got the grey and while they're true to color, it's such a light grey that it kinda just looks like a dirty white against the crisp white of the AirPods.
The product is really good. I wasn't quite as enamored with their communication during the time they were creating it.

Review.Titre: They definitely don't fall out as much…
Review.Contenu: They definitely don't fall out as much as the regular ones they get dirty if you have alot of wax in your ear for some reason I feel as the noise cancelation is off don't know why bout overall I like it bout still gonna have to give it a 4 star.

They fit really good. I just have huge ear canals so the buds don’t have rebound that contours them. But I would definitely use these on a long trip where I have to keep my AirPods on. They’re super convenient.

The ear tips seem to be fine. They’re very comfortable and do a good job of isolation. The problem I had is with the packaging. It’s simply terrible. I had to peel through glue and cardboard to get access to the ear tips. Not sure how that got by R&D.
Eartips kinda fit, but not well enough to pass the eartip fit test. case is sick, cleaning tool does its job.
These are pretty good. Fit very well. Nice and comfortable but the need better colors.
Smaller case needed, needs to be pocket sized to bring to a concert.  This case is huge.
They are definitely not falling out but still early. So far so good.
Plugs are great. They fit great and work really well with my iPods. Took about 4 weeks to get them was the only problem.

Review.Titre: Get 1 size higher than you usually wear

Review.Contenu: They are very comfortable, durable.
Fits good and feels really comfortable.
They fit great, have better isolation and bass response, and they stay in while I run!
Arrived quickly.  The earbuds were easy to install and fit comfortably inside the ear canal and don’t drop out.

Review.Titre: I Love these Ear Fidelity Units !!
Review.Contenu: I love these Ear Fidelity units !! They have enabled me to realize the full potential of my Sony WF-1000XM5 earbuds. No more weak bass due to a poor seal !! The full frequency range is produced faithfully now !! And the soft silicone material is super comfortable !!

Review.Titre: Will be used at the Gun Range
Review.Contenu: I've used electronic earmuffs for shooting for years, which are great for handguns, but depending on the rifle of shotgun, they get in the way. I finally decided to buy a pair of electronic earbud type hearing protection but looking at all the brands i know, I knew I wasn't going to pay $200 to $400 for something I wouldn't be using a lot, so I decided I wouldn't buy them. Then I found Eartune, and figured why not give them a try, after all, they have a good return policy. I could live with the price of the Eartune Hunt earbuds and the shipping was very quick. I haven't been able to go to the range yet but the fit is good. I have tried them in a loud environment and they seem to do a good job. From other reviews, I expect a lot and don't think I'll be let down.

Review.Titre: Custom plugs are comfortable and very easy to deploy!
Review.Contenu: The material appears that it will hold up well.  These custom plugs are comfortable and very easy to deploy.  I have funky ear canals [apparently] and these have changed my listening experience!   I work around a lot of noisy equipment (saws, sanders, motors) and these custom plugs fit so snug that the noise cancelling feature of my earbuds are much more effective!
FANTASTIC. I got custom tips for my 2020 Andormedas, they fit perfectly and really brought new life to these IEMs.

These foam AirPod tip replacements make all the difference in daily use. I always felt like the original silicon tips were loose and didn't fit well. I was afraid they were going to fall out at any moment when I was moving around. Comfort, security, and improved sound.  Apple AirPods should be shipping with these from the factory.

Review.Titre: Ordering is simple, & quick w/ great customer service.
Review.Contenu: Ordering was simple, placed the order and someone contacted me about when will I be sending my ear molds.  You can do it on your own but I paid $70+ to have an audiologist do it, mailed it to them and 4 to 5 weeks later custom ear tips at home.These things are amazing only now have I realized how bad the battery life is for Airpods Pros, as I am happy to leave my custom ear tips in my ears all day. Eartune's custom ear tips puts the Pro in the AirPods Pro as the given ear tips are terrible and now I can not get enough thanks to Eartune.

Review.Titre: This is an amazing company to work with…
Review.Contenu: This is an amazing company to work with when you're looking for a perfect pair of earbud adapters, custom made (when you send in professionally created molds of both your ears). They are made of surgical type rubber that's pliable enough to insert into your ear canal, while housing my new Xelento by Beyer Dynamics) perfectly, creating a seal so they stay firmly in your ears and provide for much better noise control and, an awesome sound. Their customer service? world class. Highly recommend them.

Review.Titre: Nice product. Would love to have more color choices!
Review.Contenu: Nice product. Hard to find anything else like it with a standard stem and an oval tip. Very soft and pliable silicone that doesn't cause ear soreness with prolonged use. Only suggestion: you guys should offer them in other colors besides black!

Review.Titre: Fidelity U eartips perfect for JBL Reflect Flow Pro
Review.Contenu: Love the sound of the JBL Reflect Flow Pro earbuds, but their stock eartips were uncomfortable and didn't fit well. Tried using foam eartips from a different brand, and they also felt uncomfortable. The round shape just didn't fit well in my ears. Eartune Fidelity U eartips are exactly what I was searching for: lightweight silicone, flexible and comfortable, create a great seal, and don't slide out of place. My only regret is not finding these first!! Now, I can wear my JBL earbuds all day with zero discomfort.

Eartunes are far superior to the ear plugs provided by Apple.  I bought the Beats earphones that hooked over the ear because my AirPods kept falling out during workouts.  Switching out to Eartunes has solved that problem.

I've spent years trying to find silicon tips that will stay in my ears for longer than a few minutes. Eartune's Fidelity U tips are the first tips that actually stay in place, create a good seal, and bring out the best in my IEMs. Customer support is also great—had some shipping trouble, and they promptly sent out another order same day and at no additional cost. Well done!

Review.Titre: Great customer service, high quality products!
Review.Contenu: Eartune has great customer service, they told me to get my impression redone because the Audiologist didn’t follow the directions. It took a few extra weeks to get my first AirPod Pro Custom IEM Tips, but they were totally worth it. I have since ordered another pair of AirPod Pro tips with the new adapter, a pair of shooting ear plugs, and I just ordered a set of live music ear plugs. I love the quality of the ear tips, nothing standard fits and stays in my ears, so Eartune is my best option.

Review.Titre: Only thing that has ever worked for me!
Review.Contenu: I have very oddly shaped ear canals and can literally never get earbuds to stay in — I’d tried everything! The earmolds I ordered just came in and they fit perfectly, stay easily in my ears, and have allowed me to start using my Apple AirPods for the first time. Thank you!!

Review.Titre: I was looking for foam eartips for a…
Review.Contenu: I was looking for foam eartips for a set of IEMs that only come withedium where I was hoping for a large offering considering the price.  Shopped around at a few different sites, messaged this one on some dimensions I was needing, they gave that info and I ordered.  With that, of course they offered a free return and refund if it didn't work.  But they work perfect and here we are.

Ordered foam Eartips for Airpods Pro. They were delivered in 2 days (faster than Amazon deliveries currently), and the product works great, keeping my Airpods Pros from falling out of my ear during workouts. I'm just confused why they are moving away from the ADV. Sound Branding.

Customer Service is where Eartune stands out for me.  I had left a review about memory foam eartips not fitting properly.  They immediately followed up and offered the next size down for me to try.  They worked well.  This experience led me to choosing this company for custom iem molds for my AirPod Pros.

Review.Titre: The fit is great, and the customer service is excellent.
Review.Contenu: It all started with me asking if my earbuds would work with their process. Their customer service team were polite and responsive to all my questions and concerns. The fit is what I hoped for with custom molded ear tips as well as the sleep ear plugs I got with them. I'm very happy with everything and highly recommend these guys.

Review.Titre: No longer constantly pushing my earbuds back into position!
Review.Contenu: I had custom earbuds made for my Airpod Pro 2s, and they work flawlessly. Now my wireless headphones don't fall out when I exercise or eat (chewing always used to work one or the other out of my ear), and I don't have to constantly push them back into position. I can't say enough good things about them.I also bought the case to store the earbuds with the wireless headphones. I like the case, but the earbuds don't stay in the lid compartment where they are meant to. I'd add a second strip of elastic fabric across the top half of the lid (not just the bottom half), so they stay in place, but it's not a big design problem. I just find them on top of the charging case when I unzip and open the carrying case on occasion.

Review.Titre: I bought the Fidelity U for my Sony…
Review.Contenu: I bought the Fidelity U for my Sony WF-1000 XM4 because I read in one of the review that the eartips that include are uncomfortable. Well, the original eartips for me is not uncomfortable but this Fidelity U eartips just make the whole earbuds much more comfortable to wear, better fit, and my ears don’t hurt if I wore them for long periods of time which I have with the original ear tips after 2 hours. Best part, it fit enough for me to wear while running which is why I bought the earbuds in the first place. Overall, it’s a solid investment for your Sony WF-1000XM4.

Review.Titre: Apple cheats out at the last step of production.
Review.Contenu: The original pieces that came with my airpod pro’s absolutely suck. I can’t believe that Apple which makes such great products cheaper out on the last part. I have a question for them: who cares how good a product is if it’s uncomfortable and slides out (no matter what size is used) ??  The memory foam pieces are superb. And they’re inexpensive enough to have no problem replacing them when worn out. I will be a returning customer.

Excellent products and the ordering process was straight forward.  I mailed in my impressions, the earplugs and IEM tips I ordered were a perfect fit and I am 100% satisfied with both.Questions I sent to customer service were promptly answered. Excellent across the board.

Review.Titre: Simple solution for need to remove custom earmolds to charge
Review.Contenu: They fit well, and provide the isolation I was looking for. But I don't need that isolation level all the time, just in very noisy environments. With that in mind,  my only hesitation with your custom mold's design was the need to remove them every time before I could put the airpods pro back into the case. Fortunately I've arrived at a simple solution. I have some earbud tips that fit nicely onto your white baffles -- the baffles being the white hard plastic deals that snap onto the airpods pro- which I now keep on the baffles most of the time, and THEY fit in the charging case. So for regular use I have your white baffles installed plus eartips similar to Apple's in size and performance. Then, on those occasions I need better isolation, I pop off those tips and use your custom earmolds. Very happy with this solution. Eartune might even consider shipping a few sizes of similar earbud tips as maybe an option, perhaps including a small surcharge, with your custom mold orders.

I received the ear tips in a matter of days. I ordered the medium sized ones based on their recommendation on the website. I could definitely tell a difference, but they didn’t quite seal up like I would have expected. I contacted them and they immediately sent me the next size up to ensure that I was satisfied with their product. I have to say, they make an amazing product and it is truly a game changer. My AirPods have never sounded better. It also enhances the noise canceling as well, which is a plus! I will continue to, and have already, recommend them to my friends and coworkers.

Review.Titre: AirPods slipping out? This is your solution
Review.Contenu: Found these on an ad on Instagram and I’m glad I did because earbuds are always a pain point for me when they slip out of my ear. These pretty do exactly as stated- They’re comfortable; I’ve used some of these foam ear buds for my AirPod Pros in the past and they were kinda uncomfortable after 20-30 minutes. I have these in for like two hours and they’re great - They don’t slip out my freaking ear, thank god lol, the MAIN point of me getting these- They don’t deteriorate the sound. These are dope, definitely will be buying again and if you’re debating getting them because you have problems with your AirPods slipping out your ears too? Just pull the trigger and buy these and do yourself a favor.

Review.Titre: I have the memory foam tips for air pod…
Review.Contenu: I have the memory foam tips for air pod pros. There’s no warranty but after I messaged them and explained what happened to my original pair I received 30% off on a replacement pair and they are very comfortable so  based on quality and excellent customer service I would recommend anyone to order from this company.

Review.Titre: I have used many eareplugs for surfing…
Review.Contenu: I have used many eareplugs for surfing and these are hands down the absolute BEST!!  They never fall out! I use these 3 or 4 times a week and can't imagine surfing without them. My ears thank you Eartune!!!

Review.Titre: There earbud tips for my galaxy pros…
Review.Contenu: There earbud tips for my galaxy pros work much better than what comes with the original ear buds. They are comfortable and seem to seal better plus stay better in my ears. Perfect replacement to enjoy my galaxy products. Love em. Thank you.
Sounds great, and super comfortable.The delivery lead time was quite long, but it was delivered right when they said it would so you can't beat that. Very happy with everything!
